**Star Wars - The Darksaber**

The Darksaber From The Mandalorian & The Book of Boba Fett. Replica 100%.

**Recommended Settings :**
> In Settings > Qosmetics settings > Sabers | **Override Trail Length : OFF**
> In Settings > Player Option | **Trail intensity : 1.0**
> Mod Settings > AikaTweaks  >  **Bloom : ON** | **Resolution : 0.9** | **AA : OFF** | **RR : 72**

model.description:
**Gun Saber**

**gun saber.qsaber **- has a bullet trail for the actual saber
**gun saber (no trail).qsaber** - **does not** have the saber bit, but is correctly rotated to look like a gun

**Below 0**

*brrrrrrrr* \ud83e\udd76

For those of you who have followed the development of this saber, you've probably noticed that the more complex animations are reduced to more simple ones, and the sled gone. I really wish I could've left it in, but with the new way 3.0 .blend files are handled in Unity, there just isn't any information carried over. This means no Blender animations for the way I import them. I do however have a possible solution, but it requires animating everything all over again, and I'm leaving for a bit so I just wanted to get this out here.

Big thanks to <@!569375914476044290> for helping me fix my ngon issue as well!

**As always,** reach out to me with any issues that you find!
